<TITLE> Magura police chief removed for corruption </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Magura, May 21 (bdnews24.com)Magura police superintendent Mohammad Shahriar has been relieved of his duties and asked to report to the police headquarters. Deputy inspector general (administration) Benazir Ahmed asked Shahriar to hand over his duties to his replacement on Thursday evening. According to Magura police, the police super was under investigation on charges of irregularities, corruption and highhandedness. Police headquarters security cell's assistant super Nesar Uddin came to Magura on Nov 3, 2009 to conduct the investigation. Further investigation was carried by ASP Iftekhar Uddin of the same department on May 16. After four days of investigation, the police head quarters ordered his withdrawal. However, SP Shahriar denied the corruption charges against him to journalists. "I've been transferred to the head office according to normal procedure", he said. bdnews2
